@guozhangwang - In my case, I added a serde that translates between JSON and a particular POJO type. The design was based on your [JsonPOJOSerializer](https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/streams/examples/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/examples/pageview/JsonPOJOSerializer.java) from the Kafka Streams examples , but specific to that type.

I'd be happy to see a generic Serde for JSON <-> POJO included, but I still expect there will be cases where folks need to define a project-specific Serde and it would be nice to subclass `Serdes` to include it.

I'd be open to doing the work of incorporating JsonPOJOSerializer/Deserializer into `common.serialization` as a separate PR.

@vahidhashemian There probably isn't any documentation, but the usage should hopefully be clear enough based on other test cases. The consumer tests are a little tricky because there are multiple sockets which we're trying to mock without needing to depend on the relative order of the calls (since it doesn't matter). The offset commit should come from the coordinator connection, so if you follow the template of the other tests, you should just need to add something like this:

``` java
Struct offsetCommitResponse = buildOffsetCommitResponse();
client.prepareResponseFrom(offsetCommitResponse, coordinator);
```

And you can look in `ConsumerCoordinatorTest` to figure out how to build the offset commit response.

@ewencp Not urgent, but it would be nice to see this merged into trunk/0.10.0 branches. 

